                <h1>Unraveling Air Force History: From Wings to Warfare</h1>
                <p>The history of the Air Force began during World War I, evolving from rudimentary flying units to a distinct military branch post-World War II. Key developments include the establishment of the U.S. Army Air Forces, the advent of jet technology, and pivotal roles in conflicts worldwide. Today, it stands as a symbol of air superiority and global reach.</p>
